 "bull": {
  "claim": "MaxLinear's revenue recovery is steep and real - from -61.7% YoY at the 2024 trough to +43/+48/+56% in the last three quarters on a 57% gross margin - and if operating margin merely crosses zero, the P&L rebuild does the rest.",
  "pillars": [
   "The turn is violent and consistent: revenue YoY went -61.7%, -50.0%, -40.2%, -26.5%, +0.7%, +18.3%, +55.9%, +48.0%, +43.0% across nine quarters - a completed round trip from collapse to strong growth.",
   "Gross margin 57.2% means every incremental revenue dollar is high-quality; the losses (operating margin -12.2%) are an opex-scale problem, which growth at +43% fixes mechanically.",
   "The model grades the recovery: Growth A-, Momentum A (+311% in 3 months, +501% in 12) - and a 0.39 PEG says even the 47.2x forward multiple is cheap against the earnings swing now underway."
  ],
  "catalysts": [
   "Next 2 quarters: operating margin crossing zero - the single most mechanical re-rating trigger a loss-maker has.",
   "H2 2026: interconnect/broadband design wins sustaining >=30% revenue growth into 2027.",
   "Ongoing: only 11 covering analysts - the name re-rates on discovery, not just results."
  ],
  "falsifiers": [
   "Revenue growth decelerates below +20% YoY while operating margin is still negative - the window closes.",
   "Gross margin compresses below 52% - the mix story degrades while losses persist.",
   "Operating margin still negative after two more quarters despite the +43% top line."
  ]
 },
 "bear": {
  "claim": "A $7.9B market cap for a company losing money on every line (operating -12.2%, net -25.9% trailing, ROE -27.9%), trading 221.8% above its quant buy point after +311% in three months, with the street's mean target 22.8% BELOW the price - the tape has priced profits that do not exist.",
  "pillars": [
   "Profitability grade D with nothing hidden: latest-quarter net margin -32.9%, EV/EBITDA is literally negative (-226x) - there is no E in any of the ratios; 15.6x sales is carried entirely by the top-line slope.",
   "The +43-56% growth prints lap 2024 quarters that were down 26-62% - by 2026-09 the comps normalize and the same business printing +15% will look broken against a Momentum-A price.",
   "The street's own math is the warning: mean target 22.8% below spot across 11 analysts, and the model's composite is 6.49 (rank 148 of 201) - Hold at best, while the price is 221.8% above the systematic buy point, the largest such gap in the c78q book."
